    ğŸ”¹ `bdftruncate -v` --> ğŸ“¢ Shows more information about the truncation process.
    ğŸ”¹ `bdftruncate -o <new_file>` --> ğŸ’¾ Saves the result in a new file.

ğŸ›  **Examples:**

    $ bdftruncate -n 128 original_font.bdf > truncated_font.bdf

    ğŸ”¹ Takes the first 128 characters from `original_font.bdf` and saves them in `truncated_font.bdf`.

    $ bdftruncate -u original_font.bdf > truncated_font.bdf

    ğŸ”¹ Removes unused characters from `original_font.bdf` and saves the result in `truncated_font.bdf`.

